                    <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                        <ab>
                          <lb n="1"/><rs type="institution" subtype="official" role="dedicant" key="phrourarchos" ref="#itanos"><persName type="attested" key="Philotas f. Genthios"><name nymRef="Φιλώτας">Φιλώτας</name>
                          <lb n="2"/><name nymRef="Γένθιος" type="patronymic">Γενθίου</name>
                          <lb n="3"/><placeName ref="#epidamnos" type="ethnic">Ἐπιδάμνιος</placeName></persName></rs>
                          <lb n="4"/>τῶν πρώτων
                          <lb n="5"/><w lemma="φίλος">φίλων</w> καὶ <w lemma="χιλίαρχος">χιλί<lb 
                        break="no" n="6"/>αρχος</w> καὶ <rs type="institution" subtype="official" role="dedicant" key="phrourarchos" ref="#itanos"><w lemma="φρούραρχος">φρούραρ<lb 
                        break="no" n="7"/>χος</w></rs> <persName type="divine" key="Zeus Soter">Διὶ Σωτῆρι</persName>
                          <lb n="8"/>καὶ <persName type="divine" key="Tyche Protogenes Aienaos">Τύχηι Πρ<supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied>το<lb 
                        break="no" n="9"/>γενῆι Αἰ<unclear>ε</unclear>νά<lb 
                        break="no" n="10"/><unclear>ω</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></persName>.
                          </ab>
                    </div>
                    <div type="commentary">
                        <p>La dedica a Zeus <foreign>Soter</foreign> e alla Tyche <foreign>Protogenes Aienaos</foreign> è promossa da Philotas figlio di Genthios di Epidamnos, <foreign>chiliarchos</foreign> e <foreign>phrourarchos</foreign> della base militare tolemaica di Itanos (sulla quale cf. <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_2"><title>IC</title> III 4 2-5</ref>, <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_9">9</ref>, <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_18">18</ref> e <bibl><ref target="#b1740">Spyridakis 1970</ref></bibl>) e appartenente al gruppo dei <foreign>protoi philoi</foreign> del re lagide in questione, verosimilmente Tolemeo VI (menzionato anche in <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_9"><title>IC</title> III 4 9</ref> e forse in <ref type="ins" target="#ig_xii_3_466"><title>IG</title> XII, 3 466/1390</ref>; cf. <bibl><ref target="#b319">Chaniotis 2002</ref>, p. 109</bibl>). Un altro comandante del <foreign>phrourion</foreign> tolemaico è attestato nel corso del III secolo a.C. come dedicante in <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_18"><title>IC</title> III 4 18</ref>, sebbene con il titolo lievemente differente di φρουράρχων.</p>
                <p><emph>Elementi istituzionali o altri termini rilevanti</emph>: <ref type="inst" target="#phrourarchon"><foreign>phrourarchos</foreign></ref>.</p>
                    </div>
